The British Council and Beetfreeks Collective, in partnership with Co-creation (CcHUB), have announced the launch of new narratives pilot, a co-creation lab pilot designed to prototype solutions that help stimulate more plural and diverse narratives to solve the problem of singular, out-dated narratives between Africa and the UK. This partnership would see 40 digitally savvy young professionals from both places develop prototypes that address this challenge. The programme aims to support young people to generate and disseminate a new and refreshing narrative of both places in order to foster new and stronger collaborations that would achieve new, Africa/UK understanding that unlocks new connections and contribute to the mutual benefit of both locations. The pilot is scheduled to take place between February and April 2020. The first stage of the programme would see 40 young people comprising 30 Africans and 10 British participate in two residential labs in Kigali and Birmingham to develop exciting, new ideas that contribute to new narratives between Africa and the UK. The CcHUB Design Lab, in a series of design thinking capacity development sessions, through its multi-disciplinary team of product designers and engineers would support the participants to explore the application of Human-centred Design (HCD) to create fresh, diverse and innovative solutions for richer narratives. The pilot is part of a five-year programme sponsored by the British Council and delivered by both partners is projected to strengthen Africa – UK relationship and birth a more mutual cultural, social and  economic benefit. According to the regional director, Sub Saharan Africa region of British Council, Moses Anibaba, new narratives aims to contribute to ensuring that this future relationship is based on more up-to-date, correct and complete narratives generated through new connections and strong engagement between young people in both places. Co-founder and CEO of CcHUB, ‘Bosun Tijani, added that, “With the immense opportunity that modern-day technological platforms bring, building these connections through a people to people approach provides not only a unique opportunity to co-create shared prosperity but also take collective ownership for our stories.”